00:30:16,689 --> 00:30:18,315
How am I supposed to
get the housework going...

504
00:30:18,482 --> 00:30:20,859
I want to see you when I
throw away the newspapers...

505
00:30:21,027 --> 00:30:23,404
I want to know, who drinks
coffee when and where!

506
00:30:23,571 --> 00:30:25,614
What kind of impression does that make!

507
00:30:25,781 --> 00:30:28,658
You are also interested in
having order...

508
00:30:28,826 --> 00:30:31,370
What's gotten into you anyway?

509
00:30:31,537 --> 00:30:33,163
That's Püppi.

510
00:30:34,874 --> 00:30:38,794
(Muffled noise)

511
00:30:38,961 --> 00:30:40,879
Waiter?

512
00:30:43,132 --> 00:30:45,050
They don't like us here.

513
00:30:46,844 --> 00:30:49,805
Waiter, may we perhaps
bring them SOMETHING?

514
00:30:51,015 --> 00:30:52,141
Waiter?

515
00:30:52,308 --> 00:30:54,226
Have the gentlemen ordered?

516
00:30:54,393 --> 00:30:57,437
Yes, for some time now. We
would like two calves' livers.

517
00:30:57,605 --> 00:31:00,608
- I wouldn't recommend that.
- Oh, and anything else?

518
00:31:00,775 --> 00:31:03,778
Homemade chicken soup, but I
would advise against that as well.

519
00:31:03,944 --> 00:31:05,946
And fish?

520
00:31:06,113 --> 00:31:09,533
- Then I'll take the hunter's steak.
- As you wish.

521
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:11,743
- Do you have pear Helene?
- Heinrich!

522
00:31:11,911 --> 00:31:14,079
That is our specialty.

523
00:31:14,246 --> 00:31:16,581
We serve natural pear
puree with vanilla sauce.

524
00:31:16,749 --> 00:31:18,667
Pear Helene is a poached pear with

525
00:31:18,834 --> 00:31:20,377
vanilla ice cream and chocolate sauce.

526
00:31:20,544 --> 00:31:23,338
Ours is with vanilla sauce
and is always very popular.

527
00:31:23,506 --> 00:31:25,549
Your pear is simply not
a pear Helene.

528
00:31:25,716 --> 00:31:28,593
- How about the apple pie?
- No, thank you.

529
00:31:28,761 --> 00:31:31,472
So 1 hunter's steak.

530
00:31:31,639 --> 00:31:33,807
If I hear
pear Helene one more time,

531
00:31:33,974 --> 00:31:36,685
I throw myself down
and bite into the carpet!

532
00:31:36,852 --> 00:31:38,103
Ach was!

533
00:31:38,270 --> 00:31:40,105
I have imagined your
retirement differently.

534
00:31:40,272 --> 00:31:43,108
This is my first retirement!
I am still practicing!

535
00:31:43,275 --> 00:31:47,237
I just thought... My God,
what are men insensitive!

536
00:31:47,405 --> 00:31:48,781
Everyone here can understand you.

537
00:31:48,948 --> 00:31:50,616
Unfortunately I don't
understand you at all.

538
00:31:50,783 --> 00:31:52,701
- 1 Jägerspieß.
- Thank you very much.

539
00:31:52,868 --> 00:31:55,370
If you should eat right
now, it is not very hot.

540
00:31:55,538 --> 00:31:57,915
- And mine?
- You didn't order anything.

541
00:31:58,082 --> 00:32:01,585
- Then I'll have the chicken soup.
- Chicken soup.

542
00:32:07,216 --> 00:32:09,551
Give it here, I'll do it.

543
00:32:09,718 --> 00:32:12,053
Maybe you'll let me do
something alone sometime!

544
00:32:12,221 --> 00:32:14,848
Here you go, here you go!

545
00:32:23,899 --> 00:32:26,359
I didn't say anything.

546
00:32:37,455 --> 00:32:40,166
Order yourself a
hunter's skewer.

547
00:32:40,332 --> 00:32:42,709
That's mine.
That's right here with me.

548
00:32:45,754 --> 00:32:50,254
Have you ever seen what it
looks like when you do that?

549
00:32:50,509 --> 00:32:52,427
What am I supposed to do?

550
00:32:54,763 --> 00:32:56,806
- When am I supposed to do that?
- Always.

551
00:32:56,974 --> 00:32:58,809
You've already done it 3 times here.

552
00:32:58,976 --> 00:33:01,186
Then that's
a lovable peculiarity.

553
00:33:01,353 --> 00:33:03,271
Do you know what you're doing?

554
00:33:03,439 --> 00:33:05,899
- What?
- That.

555
00:33:06,066 --> 00:33:08,234
May I clear the table?

556
00:33:08,402 --> 00:33:11,696
No, we're not finished yet.

557
00:33:11,864 --> 00:33:15,742
Should I dissolve myself then?
- It would have

558
00:33:15,910 --> 00:33:17,828
been quite fabulous if Mr. Director Lohse had

559
00:33:17,995 --> 00:33:20,706
left the director
in the company - and only Mr.

560
00:33:20,873 --> 00:33:24,793
Lohse would have remained.
- Only Mr. Lohse? "Only"?

561
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:27,587
I am Heinrich Lohse, happily married, ha-ha!, with one

562
00:33:27,755 --> 00:33:31,091
child and a regular income. What does "only" mean here?

563
00:33:31,258 --> 00:33:34,886
I just want us to be at home now instead of

564
00:33:35,054 --> 00:33:38,182
sitting in your company. Quiet and peaceful.

565
00:33:38,349 --> 00:33:41,352
- Old and fat!
- That wouldn't be the worst thing.

566
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:44,605
I will try my best.

567
00:33:48,692 --> 00:33:51,111
Excuse me,
my name is Drögel.

568
00:33:51,278 --> 00:33:53,029
I became an unwilling
witness of your conversation.

569
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:56,825
- I am in a hurry.
- I liked how you...

570
00:33:56,992 --> 00:34:00,328
There are ladies missing
everywhere who sometimes...

571
00:34:00,496 --> 00:34:02,414
Excuse me, but...

572
00:34:02,581 --> 00:34:04,499
We are a well-known confectionery company, the

573
00:34:04,667 --> 00:34:09,046
company Riegel and Klotz, formerly Seidenmann, Bielefeld.

574
00:34:09,213 --> 00:34:10,589
Well, uhm, yes, yes.

575
00:34:10,756 --> 00:34:13,216
We need ladies with joy in the matter.

576
00:34:13,384 --> 00:34:15,427
May I offer you my card...? Excuse me.

577
00:34:15,594 --> 00:34:18,597
I had it in my hand all along.

578
00:34:18,764 --> 00:34:19,931
Thank you very much.

579
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:23,060
I would be delighted to hear from you.

580
00:34:23,227 --> 00:34:25,729
One chicken soup.

581
00:34:31,569 --> 00:34:34,405
(Door opens and slams shut)

582
00:34:34,572 --> 00:34:36,949
- Heinrich?
- Don't worry. Everything is fine.

583
00:34:37,116 --> 00:34:39,159
I don't make beds, buy groceries,

584
00:34:39,326 --> 00:34:42,329
and only go up and down the stairs.

585
00:34:42,496 --> 00:34:44,873
- If I may! - Come closer.

586
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:48,251
Excuse me, Heinrich.
That wasn't what I meant.

587
00:34:48,419 --> 00:34:51,755
I know, it's not easy for you either.

588
00:34:51,922 --> 00:34:53,965
Maybe I should have helped you more.

589
00:34:54,133 --> 00:34:57,427
- What's wrong?

590
00:34:57,595 --> 00:35:00,306
- You could have your own kingdom here with us, with your family.

591
00:35:00,472 --> 00:35:02,390
- Aha?
- Just for you.

592
00:35:02,558 --> 00:35:04,851
Where no one... where no one bothers

593
00:35:05,019 --> 00:35:07,104
you, where you can be loud sometimes.

594
00:35:07,271 --> 00:35:08,855
Loud?

595
00:35:09,023 --> 00:35:11,442
Where you can be the way you want to be.

596
00:35:11,609 --> 00:35:14,236
If we tidy up a bit here...

597
00:35:14,361 --> 00:35:17,322
That could be very...

598
00:35:17,489 --> 00:35:19,866
It could be quite cozy.

599
00:35:22,202 --> 00:35:24,120
Something like crafts or something.

600
00:35:24,288 --> 00:35:28,292
And all this is going away.
Then you have space for models.

601
00:35:28,459 --> 00:35:31,879
- Hm...
- Model building...or something like that.

602
00:35:32,046 --> 00:35:35,382
Are there gentlemen retired
everywhere here in the cellars?

603
00:35:35,549 --> 00:35:38,635
Here you also have light...
and water...

604
00:35:41,013 --> 00:35:42,472
Well, what do you think?

605
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:45,768
Can't I just stay up there?

606
00:35:54,777 --> 00:35:57,237
(Mrs.

607
00:35:57,404 --> 00:35:58,738
Lohse) The Mielke sisters are coming now.

608
00:35:58,906 --> 00:36:01,033
They'll pick me up. (In a
shrill voice) Oh, Mrs. Lohse!

609
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:05,287
I didn't know your husband was home!

610
00:36:05,454 --> 00:36:07,372
Do you want to say hello?

611
00:36:07,539 --> 00:36:11,543
No. I'll stay lying here.
Very still and peaceful.

612
00:36:11,710 --> 00:36:15,463
Coffee is in the thermos flask,
sausage rolls are in the fridge.

613
00:36:15,631 --> 00:36:18,050
Did you hear?

614
00:36:18,217 --> 00:36:20,135
I heard it!

615
00:36:20,302 --> 00:36:21,594
(The doorbell rings)

616
00:36:21,762 --> 00:36:23,680
(The door opens)

617
00:36:23,847 --> 00:36:26,850
- Good day, Mrs. Mielke.
- Good day, Mrs. Lohse!

618
00:36:27,017 --> 00:36:30,729
(The ladies talk all at once)

619
00:36:30,896 --> 00:36:35,396
(A blackbird sings)

620
00:36:36,110 --> 00:36:40,072
Ach, Mrs. Lohse! I didn't
know your husband was home!

621
00:36:40,239 --> 00:36:42,157
(In a falsetto voice)
Good day, Mrs. Mielke!

622
00:36:42,324 --> 00:36:45,285
(Clears throat, then normal
voice) Nice that you're here again...

623
00:36:45,452 --> 00:36:48,079
- Are you sick?

624
00:36:48,247 --> 00:36:49,498
- My husband just lay down for a bit.

625
00:36:49,665 --> 00:36:53,001
We took some time off.
Very sensible.

626
00:36:53,168 --> 00:36:55,086
That's not quite right,
Mrs.

627
00:36:55,254 --> 00:36:57,798
Mielke.

628
00:36:57,965 --> 00:36:59,549
I am retired.
Mr. Lohse is retired!

629
00:36:59,717 --> 00:37:01,635
We didn't know that at all.

630
00:37:01,802 --> 00:37:05,138
- Why don't you come along?
- Yes, why not?

631
00:37:05,305 --> 00:37:06,848
No, no...

632
00:37:07,015 --> 00:37:10,184
We need more men for our cultural events.

633
00:37:10,352 --> 00:37:13,563
That's really very kind, but

634
00:37:13,731 --> 00:37:16,483
my wife thought I should...

635
00:37:16,650 --> 00:37:18,151
My husband doesn't like poetry readings.

636
00:37:18,318 --> 00:37:21,946
- That's something completely new!
- We did discuss,

637
00:37:22,114 --> 00:37:24,574
that you wanted to stay
home comfortably sometime.

638
00:37:24,742 --> 00:37:28,620
Well, he can still do that!
Mr. Lohse!

639
00:37:28,787 --> 00:37:31,247
Well then I'll just put
something on quickly.

640
00:37:33,625 --> 00:37:37,587
(Heavy string music, Coughing)

641
00:37:44,011 --> 00:37:47,472
(Unintelligible)

642
00:37:47,639 --> 00:37:52,139
(Clears throat and coughs again)

643
00:37:54,146 --> 00:37:56,064
My most esteemed ladies
and gentlemen.

644
00:37:56,231 --> 00:38:00,360
For the 2nd time this year
we have gathered today

645
00:38:00,527 --> 00:38:02,820
to an event of our
cultural circle gathered.

646
00:38:02,988 --> 00:38:04,906
(Clears throat)

647
00:38:05,073 --> 00:38:08,409
This afternoon is dedicated
to contemporary literature.

648
00:38:08,577 --> 00:38:11,663
It is a great pleasure,
that the most important

649
00:38:11,830 --> 00:38:15,625
representative, living representative,
the most

650
00:38:15,793 --> 00:38:19,087
important, livingest, so still alive representative
of

651
00:38:19,254 --> 00:38:21,756
modern poetry could be found, here with us
to read from his work.

652
00:38:21,924 --> 00:38:23,717
A man,
who has made literary

653
00:38:23,884 --> 00:38:27,262
history, a name that has become
a

654
00:38:27,429 --> 00:38:29,347
term worldwide: - Lothar Frohlein.
- Frohwein.

655
00:38:29,515 --> 00:38:31,475
Frohwein.

656
00:38:39,274 --> 00:38:42,735
(Silence, only Frohwein's
leather jacket squeaks)

657
00:38:50,202 --> 00:38:54,247
(Silence, only the creaking
of the leather can be heard)

658
00:38:59,211 --> 00:39:00,879
(Expectant silence)

659
00:39:03,131 --> 00:39:07,631
At the beginning I will read 22
poems from the cycle "Farewell".

660
00:39:09,429 --> 00:39:13,349
- Then...
- A little louder, please!

661
00:39:13,517 --> 00:39:15,977
Then 8 ballads from my early creative period,

662
00:39:16,144 --> 00:39:20,189
followed by the sonnet collection "The 12 Months".

663
00:39:20,357 --> 00:39:24,857
Hereupon 3 chapters
from the novel

664
00:39:25,237 --> 00:39:29,115
"Pedokles" and finally
a tragedy in 3

665
00:39:29,283 --> 00:39:32,244
acts with the title:
"Goethe in Halberstadt”".

666
00:39:32,411 --> 00:39:36,415
Then we will have the
opportunity, to speak to each other.

667
00:39:58,228 --> 00:39:59,562
Melosine...

668
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:01,356
(Hiccup)

669
00:40:04,818 --> 00:40:06,236
(Hiccup again)

670
00:40:10,407 --> 00:40:11,825
(Hiccup)

671
00:40:27,716 --> 00:40:29,634
Is that part of the recital?

672
00:40:29,801 --> 00:40:32,011
A piece of sugar always helps me.

673
00:40:32,179 --> 00:40:35,182
- He should hold his breath.
- What do you mean?

674
00:40:35,349 --> 00:40:37,601
One would have to startle him.

675
00:40:37,768 --> 00:40:39,561
Or ask something that distracts him.

676
00:40:39,728 --> 00:40:41,980
Psst!

677
00:40:42,147 --> 00:40:43,940
(Still hiccuping)

678
00:40:44,107 --> 00:40:45,858
Excuse me,
if I interrupt you.

679
00:40:46,026 --> 00:40:47,402
Heinrich!

680
00:40:47,569 --> 00:40:48,861
(Hiccup)

681
00:40:49,029 --> 00:40:52,157
What did you have
for dinner last night?

682
00:40:53,742 --> 00:40:57,287
Uhm...Kohlrabi.

683
00:40:57,454 --> 00:41:00,415
Steamed kohlrabi with fish

684
00:41:00,582 --> 00:41:05,044
sticks and... tartar sauce.

685
00:41:10,050 --> 00:41:11,468
Melosine...

686
00:41:12,678 --> 00:41:14,721
Krawehl, Krawehl!

687
00:41:14,888 --> 00:41:17,432
Dew-hazy glim by the Muses' grove!

688
00:41:17,599 --> 00:41:20,268
Haze groved dew by the Muses' glim!

689
00:41:20,435 --> 00:41:22,979
Krawehl, Krawehl!

690
00:41:23,146 --> 00:41:24,939
(Hiccup)

691
00:41:26,233 --> 00:41:30,278
(Romantic piano music)

692
00:41:47,879 --> 00:41:51,924
(Music overlays
the various conversations)

693
00:42:09,901 --> 00:42:13,446
I always thought before, that
we were living past each other.

694
00:42:13,613 --> 00:42:16,741
You've told me that 3 times already.

695
00:42:16,908 --> 00:42:19,452
I told him what I meant, and

696
00:42:19,619 --> 00:42:21,912
I thought, he had understood!

697
00:42:22,080 --> 00:42:25,625
He doesn't throw beds out
the window anymore, no!

698
00:42:27,085 --> 00:42:29,754
Now he's discussing
with Lothar Frohlein!

699
00:42:29,921 --> 00:42:33,341
- One sausage, for the lady.
- Thank you very much.

700
00:42:33,508 --> 00:42:36,219
Maybe there's also
something else besides men.

701
00:42:37,846 --> 00:42:39,347
What do you mean by that?

702
00:42:39,514 --> 00:42:42,517
One shouldn't
drive oneself crazy.

703
00:42:42,684 --> 00:42:44,435
Let them do
whatever they want.

704
00:42:44,603 --> 00:42:47,939
There are such beautiful
men..., uh, possi-bilities.

705
00:42:48,106 --> 00:42:51,484
Compared to women,
men are really uninteresting.

706
00:42:51,651 --> 00:42:54,278
Pretend he isn't even there.

707
00:42:55,405 --> 00:42:56,322
Ha!

708
00:43:01,161 --> 00:43:04,497
Caught you,
my darling! Haha!

709
00:43:04,664 --> 00:43:08,918
- That was brilliant.
- Thank you very much! Goodbye, Rita.

710
00:43:09,086 --> 00:43:13,548
I thought - I knew you were in town - it

711
00:43:13,715 --> 00:43:17,385
would be nice if we met somewhere. By chance.

712
00:43:17,552 --> 00:43:21,931
I won't bother either.
Pretend I'm not even here.

713
00:43:22,099 --> 00:43:24,726
- Do you have a wish?
- One pot of coffee.

714
00:43:24,893 --> 00:43:27,228
- 1 Coffee.
- Do you know who's sitting there?

715
00:43:27,395 --> 00:43:28,813
Where?

716
00:43:28,980 --> 00:43:32,149
There! The lady with the
light bonnet. That's Lisbeth!

717
00:43:32,317 --> 00:43:35,403
- Lisbeth Prenzler!
- Heinrich!

718
00:43:36,988 --> 00:43:38,906
Well, my fatty?

719
00:43:39,074 --> 00:43:42,285
Come on, put your glasses
on! It's me! Heinrich Lohse!

720
00:43:42,452 --> 00:43:45,121
How are you? You've gained a
bit of weight. It suits you though.

721
00:43:45,288 --> 00:43:48,582
- Is your husband here too?
- I'm not married.

722
00:43:48,750 --> 00:43:50,793
We visited you in Hamburg!

723
00:43:50,961 --> 00:43:53,213
I live in Würzburg.
For 36 years.

724
00:43:53,380 --> 00:43:56,674
No. Your son studied in
Hamburg and lived with you.

725
00:43:56,842 --> 00:43:59,219
- I don't have a son.
- But, Lisbeth!

726
00:43:59,386 --> 00:44:01,304
My name is Käthe.

727
00:44:02,973 --> 00:44:04,891
Oh...

728
00:44:07,394 --> 00:44:08,770
Käthe...

729
00:44:08,937 --> 00:44:12,273
You know what, I'm going now.

730
00:44:12,440 --> 00:44:14,358
I'll call you.

731
00:44:21,324 --> 00:44:24,535
So, I wouldn't have recognized
Lisbeth again. How is she doing?

732
00:44:24,703 --> 00:44:27,664
Uh...okay. She lives now
in Würzburg. Where is Rita?

733
00:44:27,831 --> 00:44:30,750
She had to go.
I have to hurry too.

734
00:44:30,917 --> 00:44:33,294
You certainly still have
something planned.

735
00:44:33,461 --> 00:44:36,589
Yes. But if you ask me,
I would accompany you.

736
00:44:36,756 --> 00:44:39,467
As a dutiful husband.
As a little mouse.

737
00:44:44,347 --> 00:44:46,682
So! So...
what do you want to buy?

738
00:44:46,850 --> 00:44:49,227
Oh, I want to
look around first.

739
00:44:49,394 --> 00:44:52,021
Look around... And where do
we want to look around first?

740
00:44:52,147 --> 00:44:55,066
Ah, that's interesting. Look!

741
00:44:55,233 --> 00:44:56,859
These are these pipe systems.

742
00:44:57,027 --> 00:45:00,905
We sold a lot of those
to Mexico. And to Cuba.

743
00:45:01,072 --> 00:45:03,699
I didn't even know, that
we were exhibiting here.

744
00:45:03,825 --> 00:45:08,079
The whole system works
without backflow preventers.

745
00:45:08,246 --> 00:45:09,914
Interesting, isn't it?

746
00:45:11,499 --> 00:45:14,710
The opening for the
overflow must be at the back.

747
00:45:14,878 --> 00:45:17,130
It is hard to see.

748
00:45:20,967 --> 00:45:23,594
Yes! You can see it from here.

749
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:26,180
Very interesting shopping route.

750
00:45:44,699 --> 00:45:46,367
